# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this React + Vite project following the official Vercel documentation.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` package (v1.x.x) using npm
- Updated `package.json` with the new dependency
- Updated `package-lock.json` with the complete dependency tree

### 2. Analytics Integration
**Modified: `frontend-new/src/App.jsx`**
- Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/react'`
- Wrapped the Routes component with React Fragment (`<>`) to allow multiple root elements
- Added `<Analytics />` component at the root level after Routes

## Implementation Details

The Analytics component was placed in the App.jsx file (the root component) to ensure analytics tracking works across all routes in the application, including:
- Home page (/)
- Login page (/login)
- Register page (/register)
- Dashboard page (/dashboard - protected route)

This placement follows the official Vercel documentation for React applications and ensures page views are tracked automatically for all routes.

## Framework Information
- **Framework**: React 19.2.4
- **Build Tool**: Vite 8.0.1
- **Package Manager**: npm
- **Analytics Package**: @vercel/analytics (React-specific import)

## Verification Completed
✅ Build completed successfully without errors
✅ No new linting errors introduced (existing linting issues are unrelated to this change)
✅ Package lock file updated correctly
✅ Analytics component properly integrated following React best practices

## Next Steps for Deployment
To enable analytics tracking in production:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel using `vercel deploy`
2. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Project Settings → Analytics)
3. Verify analytics tracking by checking browser Network tab for requests to `/<unique-path>/view`

## Notes
- The Analytics component is lightweight and has no visual UI
- Analytics will only track in production or when deployed to Vercel
- No additional configuration is required in the code
- The implementation preserves all existing functionality and code structure
